17) going out of the building now !  C U @ @SW_Amman @ZINCJordan if u want 2 put a bigger dent in this universe ;) cheers ! #startup #Tips
16) get out of the building ! validate ure business model and fund your startup through customer money ,, this how it shd be done! #startup
15) banks mix between SMEs & startups/scaleups ,, would you really dream of building a small business that aims to bcome a medium business ?
14) yet you keep building startups on a vanity matrix designed based on what VCs and banks asks you to do ? #useYourBrains ! #startup #Tips
13) VCs invest in < 1% of startups that pitch them, banks ask u for a business plan that they know u will never execute #startup #Tips
12) startups are not smaller versions of corporates, they need their own set of tools to grow pr to even stay alive ;) #startup #Tips
11) you say i have a "vision" ... i am thinking "hallucination" till you start showing proof of validation #startup #Tip
10) the > future tense u use describing Ur traction the < interested i get hearing about ure vision to make the world a better place :)
9) repeat after me: i am not my customer! my customer is someone who jumps after the solution i provide for a pain he/she has&pays 4 it NOW
8) if u want to win ! investment money should never fuel your living as a startup it should accelerate your growth ! #startup #Tip
7) your product is not your product, your business model is your product ! #startup #Tip
6) and the guy that threw you off the cliff is called life ;) #startup #Tip
5) but at the end if u dont build a plane u will crash! ure plane is your validated business model and ure crew is ure startup team
4) imagine being thrown off a cliff with no other way2survive but to build a plane,if u get investment that will only slow down ure falling
3) how long is ure startup runway? runway is a scarce resource: be it funding, patience of backers,team interest 2 follow through, market
2) temp discovery nature of startup ,, means you should act at speed to validate/preserve/pivot through business model assumptions #startup
1) a startup is a temp organization built only 2 discover a repeatable & scalable business model #startup #Tip
